desc: Carne com batata cremosa 🤤🎶   Ingredientes Carne acebolada - 500g de filé mignon em tiras - 2 colheres (sopa) de manteiga sem sal - 1 pitada de pimenta do reino - 1 colher (chá) de sal - 1 colher(sopa)de azeite - 2 cebolas cortada  em meia lua   Creme - 4 batatas picadas cozidas - 1 colher (chá) sal - 1 copo de requeijão  - 150g de mussarela fatiada - 1 caixinha de Creme de Leite Finalização - 1 xicara (chá) de batata palha   MODO DE PREPARO 1 - Em uma frigideira larga, aqueça a manteiga e doure a carne 2 - tempere com o sal e pimenta do reino e quando estiver dourada junte as cebolas e deixe refogar bem até murchar e passe para um refratário untado com azeite Creme 1 - Em um liquidificador bata todos os ingredientes e coloque metade do creme sobre a carne 2 - faça uma camada de mussarela e outra com o restante do creme 3 - Polvilhe o queijo ralado grosso e leve ao forno para gratinar por 10 minutos Retire e polvilhe batata palha e sirva.

desc: 1:30hour via train from London Victoria is Arundel Castle, recently re-opened for visitors and one of the most beautiful places I've ever visited in England.   Founded in 1067 by the Earl of Arundel, this medieval castle has been the home of the Dukes of Norfolk for the past 800 years, and as you learn, it becomes impossible to imagine English history without the part played by this powerful family. 📚 To name a few, the 3rd Duke of Norfolk was uncle of Anne Boleyn and Catherine Howard. The 4th Duke lost his head for planning a marriage with Mary Queen of Scots. The current Duke coordinated Charles coronation. 👑 But history is not all they offer. The rooms which once hosted Queen Victoria are divine, with special note to the Library. The outdoors are majestic. From award winning Tropical & English Gardens, to the abundant Kitchen Garden everywhere seems a painting out of a fairytale. 🏰❤️ Well worth a visit! ‼️A tip: booking in advance will save you time as the lines get quite big in spring 🌸 #arundel #arundelcastle #londonlife #londondaytrip #london #londontips
